as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="LBuo2vKL3A2V7EPNbGfz-12" value="Waiting for its development...<br>Ocelot is aimed at people using .NET running a microservices / service-oriented architecture that need a unified point of entry into their system. However it will work with anything that speaks HTTP(S) and run on any platform that ASP.NET Core supports." style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingTop=-4;fontSize=14;labelBackgroundColor=none;whiteSpace=wrap;" parent="1" vertex="1"> <mxGeometry x="828.5" y="101.5" width="450" height="115" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="LBuo2vKL3A2V7EPNbGfz-13" value="Atlanta is the core microservice using C# language and dotnet7.0. It uses event-driven architecture. Implementing CQRS in your application can maximize its performance, scalability, and security. Data is stored in the MySQL relational database, and data is retrieved through a DynamoDB non-relational database. To synchronize data between the relational database and the non-relational database, the SQS message broker is used." style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingTop=-4;fontSize=14;labelBackgroundColor=none;whiteSpace=wrap;" parent="1" vertex="1"> <mxGeometry x="828.5" y="201.5" width="450" height="117" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="LBuo2vKL3A2V7EPNbGfz-14" value="MySQL relational database. Hosted on AWS using RDS MySQL database technology. Highly available and fault tolerant, multi-az." style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingTop=-4;fontSize=14;labelBackgroundColor=none;whiteSpace=wrap;" parent="1" vertex="1"> <mxGeometry x="828.5" y="335.5" width="450" height="121" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="LBuo2vKL3A2V7EPNbGfz-15" value="DynamoDB non-relational database. Hosted on AWS. Very low latency, highly available, scalable and fault tolerant, multi-az. It is used to store the data to be updated between the relational database and the non-relational database. Contains a publich and a consumer." style="text;html=1;align=left;verticalAlign=top;spacingTop=-4;fontSize=14;labelBackgroundColor=none;whiteSpace=wrap;" parent="1" vertex="1"> <mxGeometry x="829.5" y="463.5" width="450" height="118" as="geometry" /> </mxCell> <mxCell id="LBuo2vKL3A2V7EPNbGfz-17" value="With a fleet of AWS Lambda, using C# language, dotnet8.0. Ocelot is aimed at people using .NET running a microservices / service-oriented architecture that need a unified point of entry into their system. However it will work with anything that speaks HTTP(S) and run on any platform that ASP.NET Core supports.

div.div: Atlanta is the core microservice using C# language and dotnet7.0. It uses event-driven architecture. Implementing CQRS in your application can maximize its performance, scalability, and security. Data is stored in the MySQL relational database, and data is retrieved through a DynamoDB non-relational database. To synchronize data between the relational database and the non-relational database, the SQS message broker is used.

div.div: With a fleet of AWS Lambda, using C# language, dotnet8.0. It is planned to update data between the RDS MySQL relational database and the DynamoDB non-relational database. The data that is manipulated in MySQL goes to an AWS SQS queue and the AWS Lambda trigger functions receive the data information and manipulate it as necessary (Insert, Update, Delete).
